  <div class="stack stack--8" style="margin-top: var(--sp-24);">
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip">Default</span> <span class="text-body">Neutral label for general metadata — dates, locations, or miscellaneous tags.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--charcoal">Charcoal</span> <span class="text-body">High-contrast label for dark UI surfaces or when stronger visual weight is needed.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--green">Green</span> <span class="text-body">Positive or active states — undergraduate level, open status, available places.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--outline">Outline</span> <span class="text-body">Minimal, unobtrusive label — use when the chip must not compete with nearby content.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--yellow">Yellow</span> <span class="text-body">Highlight or featured content — promoted courses, recommended options, key callouts.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--yellow-light">Yellow Light</span> <span class="text-body">Softer accent for secondary highlights; less dominant than Yellow on busy surfaces.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--violet">Violet</span> <span class="text-body">Postgraduate or research-level categorisation; also suits creative or arts-related content.</span></div>
    <div class="cluster cluster--16"><span class="chip chip--peach">Peach</span> <span class="text-body">Warm accent for events, open days, or time-sensitive announcements.</span></div>
  </div>
